description.value: Two ear-plugs of papyrus column form: one papyrus column is in semi-translucent light-blue glass. A white spiral encircles the shaft. Both the base of the shaft and the edge of the capital are outlined with opaque yellow threads. The other ear-plug is of opaque dark-blue glass; a white spiral encircles the shaft.   These ear-plugs are strung with a number of beads and pendants, most of which are glass. They include three stratified eye-pendants: one of yellow glass with a black and white eye, a duplicate with an additional prefabricated twisted cord in black and white, and a third with a black and white eye on a black ground. Stratified eye-beads include: two black and white, four with black and white eyes on a turquoise-blue ground, and one with a black and white eye on a blue ground. Others  are  turquoise-blue,  white  and brick-red, black, white and yellow and turquoise-blue, bright blue, white and brick-red. Two eye-beads have a translucent bright-blue ground with a black and white eye and prefabricated twisted cord of black and white. There are two striped barrel beads, one blue and white, the other black and white.

legal.credit_line: © The Trustees of the British Museum

description.value: Knob for a piece of furniture or ear-plug: in translucent olive-green glass, matt surface, intended for attachment to a piece of furniture. The shape, a circular convex top followed by a central concave area and terminating in another convex area, exactly follows the shape of the hard limestone knobs attached to wooden doors of houses at El-Amarna by means of a bronze nail. The front convex surface is inlaid at its centre with a prefabricated circular band of black and white cord. Within and surrounding this impressed detail small drops of opaque white, orange,  black, and turquoise-blue glass have been dropped from the  end of a mandril - essentially a spatter technique. The circumferences of the central concave area are outlined with prefabricated  white and black cord. At the centre of the under-surface is a cylindrical opening which reaches about halfway up the knob.

description.value: Gold ball earrings: a closely matching pair of disc-and-ball earrings, with thick S-curved hooks terminating in a small knob. The ball element is a complete sphere and is very well made, without any visible trace of joins other than a small 'lid' at the top of each, through which the wire hook is attached. Each ball also has a small chevron-shaped cut in the back. The hook is soldered to the back of the disc element, which is 1.1 cm in diameter. Three small gold grains decorate the join of disc and ball.    Earring (a) has suffered some damage, and the ball is slightly torn and crushed in places; (b) is in excellent condition and is very much heavier, presumably because it still contains a filling material of some kind.
